descript.abstract:
Contains basic landtype features: cays, islands, rocks, reefs, land, mangrove, foreshore.
This dataset is derived from the original Landtype250 coverage, and some attribute data has been incorporated directly, rather than by including look-up tables.
X & Y Coordinate attributes have been updated to refer to the feature centroid, based on the WGS84 datum, expressed in decimal degrees.
descript.purpose: The dataset provides information on the basic topography of the GBR region.

overview.eaover:
FEATURE_NAME - Name of the feature
LANDTYPE_DESC - Landtype Description (Domain: cay, foreshore, island, land, mangrove, null, reef, rock)
SQ_KM - Estimated area of the reef polygon in square kilometres.
GAZ_CODE - Gazetteer Location Code. The first part is latitude (degrees South). (Not available for all features.)
REEF_KEY - Reef Key that is unique for (almost) all reefs (NB. Hinchinbrook Is Reefs (x3) share the same REEF_KEY). This key is used as the primary index field in the reef250_pat and reef250_lut tables, and is a foreign key to the LANDTYPE250.REEF_UNIQUE field.
REEF_ID - Reef Identifier. Although not available for all reefs, the reef_id is unique for each labelled reef-group. It is essentially the gazetteer reef code in integer form, and is often used as a substitute reef identification number. The first two digits indicate the latitude in degrees South.
X_COORD - The longitude in decimal degrees of the centroid of the polygon feature which represents the object. Computer generated, consistent with WGS84.
Y_COORD - The latitude in decimal degrees of the centroid of the polygon feature which represents the object. Computer generated, consistent with WGS84.

procstep.procdesc: Metadata imported. Developed from individual data layers maintained by the GBRMPA: reefs, islands, rocks, cays, foreshore, mangrove, land. These were compiled in ArcInfo using overlay commands. The data was modified by AIMS to incorporate look-up table information directly into the layer's attributes.
